## Break

The **break** statement stops the loop immediately.

```javascript
for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
  if (i === 5) {
    break;  // Exit the loop when i is 5
  }
  console.log(i);
}
```

blocks.code:
for (let i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
  if (i === 5) {
    console.log('Found 5! Stopping...');
    break;
  }
  console.log('Number:', i);
}

console.log('Loop ended');

